<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n16017e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n16" href="#n16017e">N16 (VI.D.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n16all.htm#n16017e"> 17(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Schlacht ohne Morgen</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Germans would probably have tried, as they tried in 1914, to bring about a &ldquo;<mark>Schlacht ohne Morgen</mark>,&rdquo; a battle on reversed fronts modelled on Cannae. The fighting would probably have been about as severe as at Cannae, and men would have been fighting in close order, ten or twenty deep, along a hundred-mile front. No doubt it would have been over sooner, but the losses would probably have been just as great. <small> J.B.S. Haldane, <a name="CHEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHEM"><cite title="source">Callinicus</cite></a> (1925) 79</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02139e" href="c02all.htm#c02139e">VI.C.02:139(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
